quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  20,1,Ṭâ-Hâ
  20,2,We have not revealed the Quran to you ˹O Prophet˺ to cause you distress
  20,3,but as a reminder to those in awe ˹of Allah˺
  20,4,˹It is˺ a revelation from the One Who created the earth and the high heavens—
  20,5,"the Most Compassionate, ˹Who is˺ established on the Throne"
  20,6,To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth and whatever is in between and whatever is underground
  20,7,"Whether you speak openly ˹or not˺, He certainly knows what is secret and what is even more hidden"
  20,8,Allah—there is no god ˹worthy of worship˺ except Him. He has the Most Beautiful Names
  20,9,Has the story of Moses reached you ˹O Prophet˺
  20,10,"When he saw a fire, he said to his family, “Wait here, ˹for˺ I have spotted a fire. Perhaps I can bring you a torch from it, or find some guidance at the fire.”"
  20,11,"But when he approached it, he was called, “O Moses"
  20,12,"It is truly I. I am your Lord! So take off your sandals, for you are in the sacred valley of Ṭuwa"
  20,13,"I have chosen you, so listen to what is revealed"
  20,14,"‘It is truly I. I am Allah! There is no god ˹worthy of worship˺ except Me. So worship Me ˹alone˺, and establish prayer for My remembrance"
  20,15,"The Hour is sure to come. My Will is to keep it hidden, so that every soul may be rewarded according to their efforts"
  20,16,"So do not let those who disbelieve in it and follow their desires distract you from it, or you will be doomed.’”"
  20,17,"˹Allah added,˺ “And what is that in your right hand, O Moses?”"
  20,18,"He replied, “It is my staff! I lean on it, and with it I beat down ˹branches˺ for my sheep, and have other uses for it.”"
  20,19,"Allah said, “Throw it down, O Moses!”"
  20,20,"So he did, then—behold!—it became a serpent, slithering"
  20,21,"Allah said, “Take it, and have no fear. We will return it to its former state"
  20,22,"And put your hand under your armpit, it will come out ˹shining˺ white, unblemished, as another sign"
  20,23,so that We may show you some of Our greatest signs
  20,24,"Go to Pharaoh, for he has truly transgressed ˹all bounds˺.”"